Nucleotide sequencing of HIV shows the presence of a pol gene in one open reading frame [
  
    Ratner, L. et al., Nature, 313, 277(1985
  )]. Amino acid sequence homology provides evidence that the pol sequence encodes reverse
   transcriptase, integrase and an HIV protease [
  
    Toh, H. et al., EMBO J. 4, 1267 (1985
  ); 
  
    Power, M.D. et al., Science, 231, 1567 (1986
  ); 
  
    Pearl, L.H. et al., Nature, 329, 351 (1987
  )]. All three enzymes have been shown to be essential for the replication of HIV.
